OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPrison costs rule scrapped 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffor wrongly convicted      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A controversial rule which saw living  
OL,6, costs deducted from compensation paid  
OL,7, to wrongly imprisoned people has been  
OL,8, scrapped.                              
OL,10,FThe government announced the change on 
OL,11,FSunday after the case of Andrew        
OL,12,FMalkinson, who spent 17 years in jail  
OL,13,Ffor a rape he did not commit, prompted 
OL,14,Fcalls for it to be overhauled.         
OL,16,FHe welcomed the move but said he still 
OL,17,Ffaces a two-year wait for his payment. 
OL,19,FMPs said individuals whose payments    
OL,20,Fwere reduced should now be reimbursed. 
